TEXT 21

But charity performed with the expectation of some return, or with a desire for fruitive results, or in a grudging mood, is said to be charity in the mode of passion.

TEXT 22

And charity performed at an improper place and time and given to unworthy persons without respect and with contempt is charity in the mode of ignorance.

TEXT 23

From the beginning of creation, the three syllables\xc3\x91om tat sat\xc3\x91have been used to indicate the Supreme Absolute Truth [Brahman]. They were uttered by \nbr\xe2\x88\x92hma\xe2\x80\x9aas while chanting Vedic hymns and during sacrifices, for the satisfaction of the Supreme.
