TEXT 24

Thus the transcendentalists undertake sacrifices, charities, and penances, beginning always with om, to attain the Supreme.

TEXT 25

One should perform sacrifice, penance and charity with the word tat. The purpose of such transcendental activities is to get free from the material entanglement.

TEXTS 26-27

The Absolute Truth is the objective of devotional sacrifice, and it is indicated by the word sat. These works of sacrifice, of penance and of charity, true to the \nabsolute nature, are performed to please the Supreme Person, O son of P\xe2\x80\x9eth\xe2\x88\x92.

TEXT 28

But sacrifices, austerities and charities performed without faith in the Supreme are nonpermanent, O son of P\xe2\x80\x9eth\xe2\x88\x92, regardless of whatever rites are performed. They are called asat and are useless both in this life and the next.
